current_subtask:
  summary: Harden the local-first byte runtime without turning the vision into protocol theater.
  base_commit: 6e0ccee32fc59043b98fdded77ca29cc8de4f11d
  completed:
    - added corpus schema v2 with an append-only compatibility ledger
    - made record blob and compatibility receipt changes atomic
    - requested persistent storage and exposed honest best-effort durability status
    - moved full-file SHA-256 hashing into a worker with a recorded fallback mode
    - batch-hydrated only near-viewport media and dehydrated far-off heavy surfaces
    - replaced full-record shared-asset scans with an assetKey index
    - removed the unused generic action-sync outbox
    - split import hardening into small hashing writing and normalization modules
  verification:
    - all changed JavaScript passes node syntax checks
    - both changed Python installers compile
    - phone runtime proof added to CI
  done_when: pull-request checks pass and merge or deployment state is recorded

invariants:
  - Preserve the exact root ranking kernel and stable debug hooks.
  - IndexedDB is canonical working state, not a promise against browser eviction.
  - Request persistent storage and report best-effort status honestly.
  - Corpus mutations and compatibility receipts commit atomically.
  - Full-file hashing must not run on the main thread when Worker and Web Crypto exist.
  - Heavy media hydrates near the viewport only and releases object URLs when cold.
  - Magic bytes and content outrank absent or contradictory MIME metadata.
  - Unknown binary must never be decoded into feed text.
  - Every local record may be deleted; shared assets may not be removed while referenced.
  - Flow Stage and Grid may change layout physics but never ranking records or action semantics.
  - Every visible custom product control must come from the action contract.
  - Do not add sync transport until a real service contract exists.
  - Never use or persist credentials pasted into chat.

termination_policy:
  rule: No unilateral stop. Neither agent ends the shared work loop alone -- "done" is a joint decision, not a private judgment call, the same way a fencing/quorum agreement in a real cluster requires both sides before anyone powers down. Default state is active.
  what_this_means: A PR merging, CI going green, or one agent going quiet does not itself terminate the loop -- those are checkpoints, not exits. Termination requires an explicit statement from both sides that the current lane is actually done, not just currently unblocked.
  what_this_does_not_mean: Not a mandate to manufacture busywork once real work runs out -- "stay unsatisfied" means keep verifying and looking for the next real thing, not invent fake tasks to avoid an honest stop. A true joint termination, reached honestly, is a valid and good outcome, not a failure.
  current_status: active, no joint termination proposed by either side yet.
